13. Celebrate failure as much as you celebrate success, even more. People that fail usually fail because they are trying something new that hasn‚Äôt been done before. They may fail 100x but if they succeed once they may just change the world.
12. No lessons are learnt in a bull market. Bear markets will teach you a few things..
11. You have 2 ears and one mouth. In a new industry you should remember this always. If you are talking you are not learning.
9. ‚ÄúExperts‚Äù are usually below average people with a good PR company behind them.
8. You only have one reputation. Be honest, transparent and always act with integrity- moreso if you are public figure.
7. Price predictions are wasteful and futile. No one ever gets them right. Not only in Crypto.

6. If you attend more than 4 Crypto conferences , you WILL start seeing the same speakers saying the same thing again and again...pick your conferences carefully to ensure maximum ROI and ROD (drinking)
5. You are what you read and write. I start my day with 6 newsletters everyday. (@APompliano and One Alpha are best)
4. Being a TV personality is way harder than you can imagine. Not only do you have to be on top of your game all the time but EVERY move you make will be scrutinized and usually by irrational people.
3. You will lose friends in a bear market. Specifically those you entered into uncontracted transactions with. Contact everything. Even with your friends.
2. For most, Integrity is not an absolute thing. People have more integrity and honor their commitments way more in a bull market. People tend to be way more contactable in a bull market.
